<tr><td style="padding:20px 10px;border-bottom:1px dotted #66C029" valign="top"><p><font size="3" face="georgia,arial,helvetica,sans" color="#003900"><b>Welcome to Woophy</b></font></p><font size="2" face="georgia,arial,helvetica,sans" color="#003900"><p><img border="0" src="http://www.woophy.com/images/welcome/welcome_371509.jpg" alt="" title="" /></p>Hello {user_name}, thank you for joining woophy, the friendly community of over 40,000 amateur photographers, trying to create an accessible, visual, current, democratic and collective work of art comprised of a database picturing our remarkable world.<br />
<br />
For an easy start we have compiled this newsletter with a few tips and tricks to find your way around Woophy. You don&#039;t have to read it all at once, but you might want to keep it for further reference.
Any questions? Take your time to discover all of woophy&#039;s functions. Have a look at the Woophy <b><a href="http://www.woophy.com/faq" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">FAQ</a></b> and please don&#039;t hesitate to ask your Woophy ambassador (see below). And you will always find someone to help you in the <b><a href="http://www.woophy.com/forum" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">forum</a></b>. <br />
<br />
