<tr><td style="padding:20px 10px;border-bottom:1px dotted #66C029" valign="top"><p><font size="3" face="georgia,arial,helvetica,sans" color="#003900"><b>Tips and tricks</b></font></p><font size="2" face="georgia,arial,helvetica,sans" color="#003900"><p><img border="0" src="http://www.woophy.com/images/welcome/welcome_657561.jpg" alt="" title="" /></p>Now that you joined Woophy, we are waiting for you to show us your best photos. If you have several photos that altogether tell a story, why not write a <b><a href="http://www.woophy.com/member/?blogs" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">blog</a></b>?<br />
<br />
You will soon recognize, that other people will have a look at your photos, they even rate and comment them. You are welcome to rate and comment other photos as well.<br />
<br />
By rating (on a scale form one star to five stars) you can help the community to find the best or most interesting photos first.<br />
<br />
You can help by leaving a meaningful comment about his photo. This might not be an easy task, but try to take some time and write what you like and/or don&#039;t like about a photo. Getting honest and constructive comments on your photos may help you to improve your photography.<br />
<br />
Woophy also provides a <b><a href="http://www.woophy.com/forum" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">forum</a></b> with a whole lot of different topics. Don&#039;t hesitate to take a look at the threads by choosing the forum tab. You will find a list of the current discussions. If you want to talk about a new topic you can open your own thread.<br />
<br />
photo: <b><a href="http://www.woophy.com/member/Richt/photos?&amp;order_by=rating" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Richt</a></b></font></td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:20px 10px;border-bottom:1px dotted #66C029" valign="top"><p><font size="3" face="georgia,arial,helvetica,sans" color="#003900"><b>Do&#039;s and don&#039;ts</b></font></p><font size="2" face="georgia,arial,helvetica,sans" color="#003900"><p><img border="0" src="http://www.woophy.com/images/welcome/welcome_689481.jpg" alt="" title="" /></p>Please do share your photos of the world with us. All photos are welcome, especially those that give an impression of a place, how it looks and feels. Please don&#039;t use excessive digital alterations (a bit of contrast and color correction is fine), large text overlays (a small copyright notice is o.k.) and oppressive borders.<br />
<br />
Don&#039;t upload advertisements, porn, political propaganda, gory images and photos that aren&#039;t yours. This is illegal and we don&#039;t want to unlock our mean Woophy account cruncher.<br />
<br />
Your viewers may want to know a bit about your photo! So add informative titles and descriptions. Some meaningful keywords will make your photo appear when someone searches for something specific. Here&#039;s just an example, <b><a href="http://www.woophy.com/map#&amp;key=keywords&amp;val=glacier" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">glacier</a></b>. Try out for yourself!<br />
<br />
Please have a look at other Woophy user&#039;s photos! We suggest doing this on the map. You can favorite members and photos that you like. And you can discuss and ask questions by commenting on their photos - and even rate them. Many members appreciate photo critique, but keep it fair and constructive. Don&#039;t feel obliged to answer comments received.<br />
<br />
